21:42.166 --> 21:43.000
I'm fine.

21:47.875 --> 21:50.250
Thought she knew we were coming.

21:50.333 --> 21:53.083
[knock thudding]

21:54.458 --> 21:56.916
-[Rup] Have a key?
-[Sandy] Yeah.

21:57.000 --> 21:57.833
I got it.

21:59.375 --> 22:01.333
[sighs]

22:02.541 --> 22:03.875
[Rup] Come on.

22:07.375 --> 22:08.250
She changed the locks.

22:08.333 --> 22:09.916
Okay.
I gotta pee.

22:10.000 --> 22:11.250
Move!

22:11.333 --> 22:12.833
[knocks thudding]

22:12.916 --> 22:16.416
[knocks clanging]

22:16.500 --> 22:19.791
Okay, guys, let's avoid arguing, okay?

22:20.833 --> 22:22.500
Why are you looking at me?

22:22.583 --> 22:25.500
I brought her a gift, did you?

22:25.583 --> 22:27.416
[Parm] You brought her a gift?

22:27.500 --> 22:28.500
[Sandy] Yes.

22:28.583 --> 22:29.541
[Rup] Ah, she's coming!

22:29.625 --> 22:30.458
Okay.

22:31.458 --> 22:33.541
And don't make her feel judged.

22:33.625 --> 22:34.750
[all shouting]

22:34.833 --> 22:37.458
[all laughing]

22:38.541 --> 22:39.458
[Mona] You smell good.

22:39.541 --> 22:41.500
-Thank you.
-Hey, hey, hey, hey.

22:41.583 --> 22:43.916
-Come here.
-[all laughing]

22:44.000 --> 22:44.833
Oh wow.

22:44.916 --> 22:46.583
You look expensive.
Wow.

22:49.958 --> 22:51.458
Ah, sorry about the lock.

22:51.541 --> 22:53.041
The cable guy was a stalker.

22:53.125 --> 22:54.541
Oh, I gotta go.

22:55.958 --> 22:57.958
Bladder of a squirrel.

22:58.916 --> 23:00.500
Wow.
I am tripping out here.

23:00.583 --> 23:03.333
When was the last time we
were all under one roof?

23:03.416 --> 23:04.958
I don't even remember.

23:05.041 --> 23:06.875
[Rup] Oh my God!

23:06.958 --> 23:08.708
Oh yeah!
Don't look!

23:09.666 --> 23:11.916
Uh, the shower is backed up.

23:12.000 --> 23:14.416
It's okay, though, I'm on it.

23:15.375 --> 23:16.458
Flush slowly.

23:17.958 --> 23:19.333
How are the kids?

23:19.416 --> 23:20.250
Amazing.

23:21.666 --> 23:24.208
Dinesh got into gifted kindergarten.

23:24.291 --> 23:26.208
I didn't even know that was a thing.
Wow.

23:26.291 --> 23:28.125
[laughing] I know.
How are you?

23:28.208 --> 23:30.416
Uh, I'm amazing.

23:30.500 --> 23:33.125
Yeah, I'm on the last draft of my book.

23:33.208 --> 23:35.291
They're calling me the next Kiran Desai

23:35.375 --> 23:38.041
but more digestible. [laughs]

23:38.125 --> 23:39.875
-That's good.
-I got you something.

23:39.958 --> 23:40.791
Oh?

23:45.083 --> 23:46.416
I didn't know we were doing gifts.

23:46.500 --> 23:48.916
[Sandy] No, open it.

23:49.000 --> 23:52.291
-Okay.
-[paper tearing]

23:56.458 --> 23:58.791
[chuckling]

24:01.500 --> 24:04.625
"So You're Thinking of Writing a Book"?

24:04.708 --> 24:07.458
"31 Pointers for Aspiring Writers".

24:07.541 --> 24:09.625
I met the author at the
clinic's Christmas party.

24:09.708 --> 24:11.625
She was very woke, but,

24:13.083 --> 24:14.000
accessible.

24:15.791 --> 24:20.208
Only in the way white Ivy
League rich women can be.

24:21.083 --> 24:22.000
You know, if you don't want it--

24:22.083 --> 24:22.958
No, no, no, I want it.

24:23.041 --> 24:24.041
No, I'll take it back.

24:24.125 --> 24:25.708
No, it's okay.
I want it.

24:25.791 --> 24:27.583
Thank you, thank you.

24:27.666 --> 24:31.041
[sighs] I'll get that fixed.

24:31.125 --> 24:32.083
No, I got a guy.

24:32.166 --> 24:33.958
No, I'll take care of it.

24:34.041 --> 24:35.208
Dad.

24:35.291 --> 24:36.125
Upstairs?

24:37.083 --> 24:38.625
[as Dracula] Vhere he can't escape.

24:38.708 --> 24:40.208
Ha ha ha ha.

24:40.291 --> 24:42.666
-Ah!
-Ha ha.

24:42.750 --> 24:43.583
Let's go.

24:45.916 --> 24:48.125
[footsteps plodding]

24:48.208 --> 24:50.000
[paper crinkling]

24:50.083 --> 24:51.208
You look good.

24:51.291 --> 24:52.125
Shut up.

24:59.916 --> 25:01.166
You clearly do.

25:04.000 --> 25:04.958
How could you not tell me?

25:05.041 --> 25:07.708
We're practically Siamese Twins.

25:08.833 --> 25:09.708
You're seeing someone!

25:09.791 --> 25:10.916
I want a name.

25:11.000 --> 25:11.833
I want a name.

25:11.916 --> 25:13.500
Is the sex good?
Is the--

25:13.583 --> 25:16.666
-Mona.
-[long hushing]

25:16.750 --> 25:17.583
Dear God.

25:18.791 --> 25:21.208
[Mona sighs]

25:24.750 --> 25:25.750
Oh my God.

25:29.125 --> 25:31.458
What?
What is this?

25:31.541 --> 25:32.375
-Oh!
-[hockey stick clatters]

25:32.458 --> 25:33.791
Oh my God!

25:33.875 --> 25:35.458
Oh my God!
Shit!

25:35.541 --> 25:37.916
-Shit, help me!
-There's a reason I'm real estate agent

25:38.000 --> 25:39.208
and not a doctor.

25:39.291 --> 25:40.500
I'm not good with this stuff, Sandy.

25:40.583 --> 25:42.166
Hold it.
Hold it!

25:42.250 --> 25:44.166
-Okay, higher.
-I'd rather not.

25:44.250 --> 25:45.708
[Sandy] Oh my God.

25:45.791 --> 25:48.083
That's so like her.

25:48.166 --> 25:49.291
She brings him home without a plan

25:49.375 --> 25:50.875
and rigs up some contraption.

25:50.958 --> 25:52.875
Okay, I know how this looks,

25:52.958 --> 25:56.500
but I researched it and he's fine.

25:56.583 --> 25:59.750
-You call this fine?
-Here, I got it.

26:00.708 --> 26:02.958
It's the right solution.

26:03.041 --> 26:04.208
Where'd you get it?

26:04.291 --> 26:06.958
[Mona] My friend Omar is an RN.

26:07.041 --> 26:08.250
You mean my friend Omar?

26:08.333 --> 26:09.458
The guy who used to sell weed?

26:09.541 --> 26:11.666
He still sells weed.

26:11.750 --> 26:14.833
But, Omar gave me some good pointers.

26:16.000 --> 26:16.916
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

26:17.000 --> 26:18.000
-Hey, hey.
-[Sandy] Papa?

26:18.083 --> 26:19.166
[Rup] He's wakin' up.

26:19.250 --> 26:20.166
-Is he waking up?
-[Sandy] Papa.

26:20.250 --> 26:22.916
[Parm] No, it's just a reflex.

26:25.958 --> 26:29.000
We're bringing him back to the hospital.

26:29.083 --> 26:31.458
Sandy, if we take him back,

26:31.541 --> 26:32.666
they're just gonna let him die.

26:32.750 --> 26:35.041
They're not gonna hook
him up to any machines. Nothing.

26:35.125 --> 26:37.416
He does not wanna be
forced to live like this.

26:37.500 --> 26:39.166
He signed two forms.

26:41.083 --> 26:42.166
This is criminal.

26:42.250 --> 26:46.416
[laughs] I'm keeping our father alive.

26:46.500 --> 26:48.000
How is that wrong?

26:55.458 --> 26:58.000
Well, if Dad wakes up.

26:58.083 --> 26:59.333
If he wakes up.

27:00.666 --> 27:03.458
It's highly possible
he could be brain dead.

27:03.541 --> 27:05.875
At the very least paralyzed.

27:07.333 --> 27:10.625
You don't know that for sure, Parm.

27:10.708 --> 27:13.416
All I'm saying is that
we give him a chance

27:13.500 --> 27:14.375
and we wait.

27:14.458 --> 27:15.375
For what?

27:16.875 --> 27:18.541
An epiphany.

27:18.625 --> 27:22.791
[distant foreign language]

27:22.875 --> 27:24.750
[groans] No! No!

27:24.833 --> 27:26.041
[in Punjabi] …and then when the
congregation comes in,

27:26.125 --> 27:27.333
they will come this way through this room,
bow down here.

27:27.416 --> 27:29.333
Puaji, Puaji, no.
I'm sorry.

27:29.416 --> 27:31.666
No.
I will not let you hijack this house.

27:31.750 --> 27:32.583
[Parm] Calm down.

27:32.666 --> 27:36.666
[in Punjabi] Parminder,
oh my good boy, my Parmi.

27:36.750 --> 27:38.458
[in Punjabi] I haven’t slept.

27:38.541 --> 27:41.750
I just want to host the prayers here,
for your father!

27:41.833 --> 27:44.166
[in English] Three days of God's prayers.

27:44.250 --> 27:46.541
Three days of a free-for-all
where every Desi in Regina

27:46.625 --> 27:49.000
comes over and eats our food and gossips.

27:49.083 --> 27:49.916
That's what it is.

27:50.000 --> 27:51.166
-[Sandy] Whoa, whoa, whoa.
-[Parm] Come on.

27:51.250 --> 27:52.833
-[Sandy] Mona, come on.
Have some respect.

27:52.916 --> 27:54.083
[Mona] I am just being honest.

27:54.166 --> 27:55.041
-[Rup] I like the honesty…
-[Puaji gasps]

27:55.125 --> 27:55.958
…not in front of everyone.

27:56.041 --> 27:56.958
-Oh my God.
-[Rup] Oh God.

27:57.041 --> 27:58.750
[Auntie moans]

27:58.833 --> 28:00.541
[Sandy] Parm, she doesn't look good.

28:00.625 --> 28:02.208
-[Parm] Water.
-[Sandy] Is she okay?

28:02.291 --> 28:04.666
[Sandy in Punjabi]
We are here to help, Auntie.

28:04.750 --> 28:06.125
[coughing]

28:06.208 --> 28:09.541
[in Punjabi] Sandy, my wise girl.

28:09.625 --> 28:13.125
[in English] My brother needs
God and prayer.

28:13.208 --> 28:15.750
Our father needs peace and quiet.

28:15.833 --> 28:18.791
[in Punjabi] Auntie, can’t we do this
prayer at the temple?

28:18.875 --> 28:22.541
[in Punjabi] No, no, no my boy, no!

28:24.041 --> 28:29.500
[in Punjabi] My brother needs to
hear the Guru’s pure words,

28:29.583 --> 28:31.083
continuously for three days.

28:31.166 --> 28:33.041
[Rup in English] I got water. I got water.

28:33.125 --> 28:36.708
[in Punjabi] Auntie, drink water.

28:36.791 --> 28:37.666
Let her do the <i>paath</i>.

28:37.750 --> 28:39.333
You guys were conveniently not present

28:39.416 --> 28:41.125
when she did the <i>paath </i>last year.

28:41.208 --> 28:42.875
Or the one before that.
Or the one before that.

28:42.958 --> 28:44.666
Or the one before that. Okay?

28:44.750 --> 28:49.041
[in Punjabi] Manjit, Manjit, girl,
my good girl, listen to me.

28:49.125 --> 28:49.958
No!

28:50.041 --> 28:51.333
Puaji, I'm putting my foot down.

28:51.416 --> 28:52.458
This is my house.

28:52.541 --> 28:56.291
This house, actually,
belongs to all of us.

28:56.375 --> 28:58.166
And I say she should do it.

28:58.250 --> 29:00.791
[Mona scoffs]

29:00.875 --> 29:01.708
I agree.

29:03.291 --> 29:04.125
Yeah.

29:05.458 --> 29:06.500
Okay.

29:06.583 --> 29:09.000
[laughs] Okay.

29:09.083 --> 29:10.166
Well, guess what?

29:10.250 --> 29:13.375
I didn't wanna do this to you guys, but,

29:13.458 --> 29:14.916
you leave me no choice.

29:15.000 --> 29:17.000
This is what happens.

29:17.083 --> 29:18.875
Where the hell?

29:20.125 --> 29:21.500
Shit!

29:21.583 --> 29:23.083
-[rumbling]
-[Mona shouts]

29:23.166 --> 29:24.000
Okay!

29:25.125 --> 29:26.208
-Rup!
-What?

29:26.291 --> 29:27.125
-Ow!
-[keys jangling]

29:27.208 --> 29:28.041
Come!

29:29.125 --> 29:31.708
Okay. All right.

29:31.791 --> 29:33.791
[in Punjabi] God is Truth. God is Truth.
[in English] I don't know.

29:33.875 --> 29:34.708
[in Punjabi] It’s okay. It’s okay.

29:34.791 --> 29:35.750
-[in English] Let's go.
-No.

29:35.833 --> 29:37.833
We're not indulging this, Parm.

29:37.916 --> 29:39.166
Puaji, call me if you need anything.

29:39.250 --> 29:40.083
[door slams]

29:40.166 --> 29:42.791
[in Punjabi] Oh my sweet boy!

29:42.875 --> 29:45.875
[in Punjabi] May you live well, stay well,
have a long, long life.

29:45.958 --> 29:48.333
-[Parm laughing]
-[in Punjabi] Go.

29:48.416 --> 29:50.916
[in Punjabi] You go, too, my good girl.
You are a wise girl. Go. Go!

29:51.000 --> 29:53.083
[in Punjabi] What are you
still doing here? Go, go.

29:53.166 --> 29:54.833
[in Punjabi] God is Truth.

29:56.625 --> 30:01.958
[in Punjabi] Priest, quickly, before Mona
returns, let’s start the prayers!

30:02.041 --> 30:05.375
Then what can they do after that?
First, let’s move everything,

30:05.458 --> 30:09.958
Pick up that table.
Priest, don’t spill my water.

30:10.041 --> 30:11.916
Okay, take this table over there.

30:12.000 --> 30:17.833
Pick up the cushions. Here, I will pass
them to you. Here you go.

30:18.458 --> 30:19.666
[Sandy] Mona, where are we going?

30:19.750 --> 30:21.041
[Mona] You'll see when we get there.

30:21.125 --> 30:22.750
Because if I tell you now,
it's gonna be a thing.

30:22.833 --> 30:23.833
[Rup] I'm not following anybody.

30:23.916 --> 30:26.000
I'm the boss of me, okay?

30:26.083 --> 30:28.625
[Parm] Just tell us where we're going.

30:28.708 --> 30:31.125
[Sandy] Where are we going?

30:31.208 --> 30:32.041
[Mona] Hi.

30:32.125 --> 30:34.375
We have an appointment with Mr. Maloney.

30:34.458 --> 30:36.041
Last name's Ghumun.

30:37.500 --> 30:40.416
I'm so sorry, but it
wasn't noted in our system

30:40.500 --> 30:42.125
and he's in meetings all day.

30:42.208 --> 30:43.041
Can you come back tomorrow?

30:43.125 --> 30:44.708
-Not a problem.
-No. We can't.

30:44.791 --> 30:47.333
My siblings flew into
Regina for this meeting.

30:47.416 --> 30:48.833
We don't actually have an appointment.

30:48.916 --> 30:49.958
My sister, she's just
very triggered right now.

30:50.041 --> 30:50.875
[fist thuds]

30:50.958 --> 30:52.041
-Mona!
-You can't go in there. Ma'am!

30:53.166 --> 30:54.000
Shit.

30:58.083 --> 30:59.375
[man] Definitely.

30:59.458 --> 31:00.458
Jason.

31:00.541 --> 31:02.750
Jason, I'm gonna have to call you back.

31:02.833 --> 31:04.250
I'll get that answer for you, bud.

31:04.333 --> 31:05.916
Okay. Okay, buh bye.

31:06.000 --> 31:07.333
I'm so sorry, Mr. Maloney.

31:07.416 --> 31:09.708
I told her you were occupied.

31:09.791 --> 31:10.666
That's okay, Rene.

31:10.750 --> 31:11.750
No problem.

31:11.833 --> 31:14.083
Give us a minute, though.

31:14.166 --> 31:15.541
Should I invite the rest in?

31:15.625 --> 31:18.166
[Mr. Maloney] You want the rest?

31:18.250 --> 31:20.333
Yes, invite them in, Rene.

31:20.416 --> 31:21.333
Go ahead.

31:22.916 --> 31:25.291
[metal clanging]

31:25.375 --> 31:26.541
Mona.

31:26.625 --> 31:27.458
Brent.

31:28.458 --> 31:29.583
Hello.

31:29.666 --> 31:31.000
We're very sorry for this intrusion.

31:31.083 --> 31:32.541
That's all right. Brent Maloney.

31:32.625 --> 31:33.750
-Sandy.
-Hi, Sandy.

31:33.833 --> 31:35.083
-Pleasure.
-Please take a seat.

31:35.166 --> 31:37.416
-Hi. Rup.
-Hey, Rup. Nice to meet you.

31:37.500 --> 31:38.750
-Brent Maloney.
-Sorry about this.

31:38.833 --> 31:40.166
-Well that's all right.
-Parm.

31:40.250 --> 31:43.083
Hey, Parm, I think I've
talked to you on the phone.

31:43.166 --> 31:44.625
Sit down, please.

31:44.708 --> 31:46.291
Everyone just stay nice and comfortable.

31:46.375 --> 31:47.791
Or get comfortable.

31:47.875 --> 31:49.375
Thanks for coming.

31:51.625 --> 31:53.458
Hi. So.

31:53.541 --> 31:54.791
What can I do for you all?

31:54.875 --> 31:57.250
Well, my siblings and
I have power of attorney

31:57.333 --> 31:59.875
over our father's accounts,
and so we would like to know

31:59.958 --> 32:01.083
the contents of his will.

32:01.166 --> 32:03.000
Has your father passed away?

32:03.083 --> 32:05.791
-[Sandy] No, he hasn't.
-He hasn't. He's had a serious stroke.

32:05.875 --> 32:07.125
He's in a coma.

32:09.166 --> 32:10.458
I'm really sorry about this.

32:10.541 --> 32:12.541
Mona, what're you doin'?

32:15.583 --> 32:16.458
Mister…

32:16.541 --> 32:18.833
-[Brent] Maloney.
-Maloney.

32:18.916 --> 32:25.250
Hypothetically speaking,
if the house belongs to me

32:25.333 --> 32:27.833
and our father's in a
state of unresponsiveness,

32:27.916 --> 32:31.541
then I would have full authority
on whatever takes place

32:31.625 --> 32:33.583
inside that house, correct?

32:33.666 --> 32:36.583
If the house is solely
in your name, then yes,

32:36.666 --> 32:38.666
you can decide what
takes place inside of it

32:38.750 --> 32:39.625
anytime you want.

32:39.708 --> 32:43.208
Why do you care so much about the <i>paath</i>?

32:43.291 --> 32:45.250
Because I need to protect myself.

32:45.333 --> 32:48.125
Because I will not be bamboozled.

32:48.208 --> 32:50.583
-No on is bamboozling you.
-Bamboozled?

32:50.666 --> 32:52.666
-Choice of language.
-Are you kidding?

32:52.750 --> 32:53.625
Are you kidding me?

32:53.708 --> 32:54.833
You guys come in here.

32:54.916 --> 32:56.625
And whatever.
You guys are fancy, bossy people--

32:56.708 --> 32:57.541
No, no, no, no. Hold on a second.

32:57.625 --> 32:59.916
We come in here?
You're the one that dragged us into this--

33:00.000 --> 33:01.875
[Mona] But you guys come to
the house and then it's like,

33:01.958 --> 33:03.125
it's your way or the highway--

33:03.208 --> 33:04.541
I wanna know. I wanna know.
I wanna know.

33:04.625 --> 33:05.500
Whoa, whoa, whoa. I'm sorry.

33:05.583 --> 33:07.291
-He wants to know.
-I wanna know. We're here.

33:07.375 --> 33:09.791
-It's our way or the highway?
-Let her just say--

33:09.875 --> 33:11.166
I'm pretty sure we had no
idea where we were going.

33:11.250 --> 33:14.458
[all chattering over each other]

33:14.541 --> 33:17.250
[Brent] Okay. Okay.

33:17.333 --> 33:19.416
Let's just take a breath.

33:21.041 --> 33:23.458
Yes, let's all take a breath.

33:24.333 --> 33:29.208
I know how difficult it is
to care for an aging parent.

33:29.291 --> 33:30.666
Even in good times.

33:30.750 --> 33:33.041
But this particular
situation is not as uncommon

33:33.125 --> 33:35.375
as you might think.

33:35.458 --> 33:38.125
So, all four of you do
have power of attorney,

33:38.208 --> 33:41.875
so, therefore, I am
legally bound to disclose

33:41.958 --> 33:44.625
all the contents of your father's assets,

33:44.708 --> 33:46.250
if it's being requested.

33:46.333 --> 33:49.250
Which I believe Mona is requesting.

33:50.125 --> 33:50.958
Yeah.

33:51.041 --> 33:56.041
All right, well then let's
get this will popped up here.

33:56.666 --> 33:59.875
[keyboard clacking]

33:59.958 --> 34:00.791
Okay.

34:00.875 --> 34:05.291
Well, let's just go over
all the smaller points here.

34:06.375 --> 34:11.250
All assets, from the house,
to the car, to all monies

34:11.333 --> 34:14.833
is to be passed to Parminder Singh Ghumun.

34:16.750 --> 34:18.625
[Sandy And Mona] What?

34:18.708 --> 34:19.708
Of course.

34:28.041 --> 34:29.791
Parents sometimes do it this way.

34:29.875 --> 34:34.791
It's a bit of a simpler task
in divvying up all the assets.

34:45.625 --> 34:47.375
[Rup] Are those? [clears throat]

34:47.458 --> 34:48.458
Are those chocolates?

34:48.541 --> 34:50.041
[Brent] Yeah.

34:50.125 --> 34:51.375
I'm just gonna grab one of these.

34:51.458 --> 34:52.291
Excuse me.

34:54.500 --> 34:55.333
Anything else?

34:55.416 --> 34:56.375
[Rup] Guess that's it.

34:56.458 --> 34:58.458
Well, thanks for stopping in.

34:58.541 --> 34:59.375
[Parm] Thank you.

34:59.458 --> 35:00.458
Thank you.

35:02.333 --> 35:04.416
[Rup] Thank you, Brent.

35:06.833 --> 35:07.875
[door closes]

35:10.166 --> 35:13.000
-[exhales slowly]
-[tense music plays]

35:13.083 --> 35:14.416
[inaudible]

35:15.958 --> 35:18.500
[cars passing]

35:31.916 --> 35:34.500
[car creaking]

35:52.083 --> 35:53.625
Pull in here.

35:53.708 --> 35:54.541
[Rup] Here?
What do you mean here?

35:54.625 --> 35:57.833
-Here. Here, here. Pull in here.
-[Rup] Okay.

35:57.916 --> 36:01.291
[loud rock music plays]

36:01.375 --> 36:02.500
[Mona] Congratulations.

36:02.583 --> 36:06.958
You get all of Dad's money,
now you get a beer.

36:07.041 --> 36:09.125
[Parm] Don't you think we
should be getting back to Dad?

36:09.208 --> 36:11.083
Puaji gets to play doctor.

36:11.166 --> 36:12.458
Give her a moment to shine.

36:12.541 --> 36:14.125
Susie!

36:14.208 --> 36:15.041
Karen!

36:16.166 --> 36:17.000
Okay, um.

36:17.916 --> 36:20.166
A pitcher of beer, please?

36:20.250 --> 36:21.416
Wait, you know what?

36:21.500 --> 36:22.500
Make it two.

36:23.666 --> 36:25.500
-Okay.
-Confession.

36:25.583 --> 36:28.000
This place smells like pee.

36:29.083 --> 36:31.250
When I was 15, I snuck in
here and I got the whole bar

36:31.333 --> 36:33.208
to sing "Oh Canada".

36:33.291 --> 36:34.833
Bet you I can do it again.

36:34.916 --> 36:36.333
We believe you.

36:40.083 --> 36:42.416
So, tell me the truth, Parm.

36:42.500 --> 36:45.208
You knew about the will, right?
Dad told you?

36:45.291 --> 36:46.125
No.

36:48.000 --> 36:49.916
I can read your mind, kid.

36:50.000 --> 36:52.208
We're practically Siamese twins.

36:52.291 --> 36:53.875
Tell me the truth. Look at my face.

36:53.958 --> 36:55.708
Look at my face.

36:55.791 --> 36:58.000
You knew about the will, right?

36:58.083 --> 36:58.916
No.

37:02.666 --> 37:04.416
I don't know why you're so surprised.

37:04.500 --> 37:06.333
This is the golden boy.

37:06.416 --> 37:07.916
-The three of us can't compete.
-That's not true.

37:08.000 --> 37:08.833
[Sandy And Mona] That's true.

37:08.916 --> 37:11.500
It's totally true.
You wear a turban, you went to Oxford.

37:11.583 --> 37:12.708
You make more money than I do.

37:12.791 --> 37:14.375
-You're a doctor.
-So is Sandy.

37:14.458 --> 37:17.000
Yeah, but she's a girl
and Dad's a misogynist.

37:17.083 --> 37:20.083
The kind of misogynist
that let the boy twin

37:20.166 --> 37:23.250
go to hockey camp all summer and,
as I remember correctly,

37:23.333 --> 37:26.666
the girl twin had to stay
at home under house arrest.

37:26.750 --> 37:28.625
Because she's a girl.

37:28.708 --> 37:33.250
Said the girl who lit
the rug on fire. [laughs]

37:33.333 --> 37:35.416
It was a flammable
polyester piece of shit,

37:35.500 --> 37:36.333
-and it was an accident.
-What?

37:36.416 --> 37:39.250
It was silk and it was an heirloom.

37:39.333 --> 37:41.875
-[Rup] It was an heirloom.
-Can I get a water, please? Thanks.

37:41.958 --> 37:42.958
[Mona] Well I did my time.

37:43.041 --> 37:44.958
Dad tied me up to the
balcony for that incident.

37:45.041 --> 37:46.125
Yeah, yeah, no.

37:46.208 --> 37:47.583
That's when it snowed and you--

37:47.666 --> 37:48.500
Frostbite.

37:48.583 --> 37:49.583
[Rup] Ah yeah, the frostbite.

37:49.666 --> 37:51.541
[Mona] It was coldest June on record.

37:51.625 --> 37:53.125
[Sandy] No, it wasn't.
It wasn't that cold.

37:53.208 --> 37:54.666
[Mona] Yeah, it was! You know, my
fingers are still tingly.

37:54.750 --> 37:55.708
Look.

37:55.791 --> 37:57.375
I'll be right back.

37:57.458 --> 37:58.291
[phone buzzing]

37:58.375 --> 38:00.458
I gotta call my kiddos.

38:07.500 --> 38:10.083
[beer pouring]

38:18.041 --> 38:20.458
Mona, please don't hate me.

38:24.333 --> 38:25.166
I don't.

38:27.458 --> 38:29.625
Dad was too hard on you.

38:30.666 --> 38:32.750
Couldn't go. Bathroom's disgusting.

38:35.125 --> 38:38.000
[fist thumps]

38:38.083 --> 38:39.416
Um, excuse me?

38:40.250 --> 38:42.625
Can I have your attention please?

38:42.708 --> 38:44.291
Hey. Hey, hey!

38:44.375 --> 38:45.208
Shut up!

38:47.000 --> 38:50.250
Our cancer-ridden father is in a coma.

38:50.333 --> 38:51.708
It's okay.

38:51.791 --> 38:53.041
He's an asshole.

38:53.125 --> 38:56.625
But, he came to this great
country with no money

38:56.708 --> 38:59.041
and a young wife and a dream

38:59.875 --> 39:03.541
of opening up his own grocery store.

39:03.625 --> 39:04.833
So.

39:04.916 --> 39:06.750
In honor of Gurpreet Singh Ghumun

39:06.833 --> 39:09.916
and every other immigrant who
is freezin' their asses off

39:10.000 --> 39:11.125
in Regina,

39:11.208 --> 39:15.250
I would like to sing one
of his favorite ditties.

39:15.333 --> 39:16.333
Please join.

39:18.416 --> 39:23.416
<i>♪ Oh Canada ♪</i>

39:23.791 --> 39:27.541
<i>♪ Our home on native land ♪</i>

39:27.625 --> 39:28.916
Don't be shy!

39:29.000 --> 39:32.000
<i>♪ True patriot love ♪</i>

39:33.000 --> 39:34.166
Oh yeah, Rup!

39:34.250 --> 39:37.875
<i>♪ It all our sons command ♪</i>

39:37.958 --> 39:39.000
Yeah!

39:39.083 --> 39:41.875
<i>♪ With glowing hearts ♪</i>

39:41.958 --> 39:44.375
<i>♪ We see thee rise ♪</i>

39:44.458 --> 39:48.583
<i>♪ The true North strong and free ♪</i>

39:48.666 --> 39:49.833
Ba ba doo.

39:49.916 --> 39:52.708
<i>♪ From far and wide ♪</i>

39:52.791 --> 39:55.458
<i>♪ Oh Canada ♪</i>

39:55.541 --> 40:00.583
<i>♪ We stand on guard for thee ♪</i>

40:01.583 --> 40:04.458
<i>♪ God keep our land ♪</i>

40:04.541 --> 40:05.708
[Mona] Yeah!

40:06.875 --> 40:11.458
<i>♪ Glorious and free ♪</i>

40:11.541 --> 40:14.875
<i>♪ Oh Canada ♪</i>

40:14.958 --> 40:18.166
<i>♪ We stand on guard ♪</i>

40:18.250 --> 40:19.500
<i>♪ For ♪</i>

40:19.583 --> 40:21.750
<i>♪ Thee ♪</i>

40:21.833 --> 40:25.000
<i>♪ Oh Canada ♪</i>

40:25.083 --> 40:28.458
<i>♪ We stand on guard ♪</i>

40:28.541 --> 40:29.916
<i>♪ For ♪</i>

40:30.000 --> 40:31.458
<i>♪ Thee ♪</i>

40:31.541 --> 40:34.333
[all shouting]
[all clapping]

40:34.416 --> 40:36.125
Drinks on this guy!

40:38.875 --> 40:41.083
[man 1] Fuck you, Paki!

40:41.166 --> 40:42.125
[man 2] Oh shit.

40:42.208 --> 40:43.125
What did you call me?

40:43.208 --> 40:44.833
Hey, let's get this mother fucker!

40:44.916 --> 40:47.500
[all cheering]

40:52.875 --> 40:56.708
[singing in Punjabi]

41:02.875 --> 41:04.208
[Parm] Go straight up stairs.

41:04.291 --> 41:05.541
-[Mona] I didn't drink!
-[Parm] Come on.

41:05.625 --> 41:07.208
[continues singing in Punjabi]

41:07.291 --> 41:10.041
[all whispering]

41:11.583 --> 41:12.416
No!

41:15.291 --> 41:17.166
[in Punjabi] Where did you all go?

41:17.250 --> 41:19.583
[Sandy in Punjabi]
We went to a restaurant.

41:19.666 --> 41:22.666
[in Punjabi] What’s wrong with her?
Why is she falling everywhere?

41:22.750 --> 41:24.250
[in English] Oh, Puaji, bad sushi.

41:24.333 --> 41:27.125
[in Punjabi] Well, then keep going to
restaurants to eat, why don’t you!

41:27.208 --> 41:28.541
[in English] Mm hm, lesson learned.

41:28.625 --> 41:29.458
Puaji!

41:30.625 --> 41:32.125
Continue.

41:32.208 --> 41:34.458
This house isn't even mine.

41:35.458 --> 41:38.208
I have no authority here.

41:38.291 --> 41:41.291
[chuckles] Far out.

41:43.708 --> 41:47.375
[in Punjabi] Auntie, shall I make us
some tea? With a bit of ginger?

41:49.000 --> 41:50.291
[in Punjabi] Okay, three minutes.

42:08.375 --> 42:11.208
[high-pitched voice] Daddy? [snorts]

42:12.250 --> 42:14.666
[snickering]

42:18.666 --> 42:23.000
What are you doing, Daddy? [snorts]

42:31.500 --> 42:34.666
[normal voice] I have a very strong urge
to kick you in the face.

42:34.750 --> 42:39.208
Cut off your hair, you piece
of shit father, you asshole,

42:39.291 --> 42:42.166
big-nosed, little [grunts].

42:42.250 --> 42:43.083
Mona?

43:01.291 --> 43:04.625
[beads rattling]

43:04.708 --> 43:09.291
First thing tomorrow morning,
we're taking Dad back to the hospital.

43:15.166 --> 43:17.250
Let me make some calls.

43:19.208 --> 43:21.041
We'll see what happens.

43:26.333 --> 43:28.625
You always take her side.

43:35.083 --> 43:37.500
[soft music plays]

43:38.666 --> 43:41.250
[cars passing]

43:47.250 --> 43:50.000
[car passing]

43:52.750 --> 43:55.666
[melancholy music plays]

44:24.083 --> 44:27.166
[indistinct chatter]

44:38.916 --> 44:42.750
[man singing in Punjabi]

44:44.375 --> 44:47.625
[Pakistani folk music plays]

45:23.833 --> 45:25.083
[indistinct] …Parm.

45:25.166 --> 45:26.833
I have three sisters
for him to choose from.

45:26.916 --> 45:27.750
Tell him.

45:29.041 --> 45:31.458
Right away, Auntie G.
Three of them? That's good.

45:31.541 --> 45:34.833
[Pakistani folk music plays]

45:54.833 --> 45:58.541
Oh yeah. Regina gumbo.

45:58.625 --> 46:01.250
Never ceases to amaze me.

46:01.333 --> 46:02.916
Well, anytime someone
uses the dishwasher

46:03.000 --> 46:04.625
or laundry or toilet,

46:04.708 --> 46:06.125
it just backs up everywhere.

46:06.208 --> 46:07.791
It's disgusting. I'm so sorry.

46:08.583 --> 46:09.625
You know,

46:09.708 --> 46:11.708
plumbing's like the arteries of the heart.

46:11.791 --> 46:14.750
If you abuse it, you will lose it.

46:14.833 --> 46:16.458
Never heard that analogy before.

46:16.541 --> 46:17.666
Hm.

46:17.750 --> 46:19.666
Just leave her with me.

46:21.375 --> 46:24.208
Sure thing. She's all yours.

46:24.291 --> 46:25.875
I'm gonna step out.

46:29.791 --> 46:30.750
[Parm] Careful.

46:30.833 --> 46:31.750
Puaji!

46:31.833 --> 46:34.708
Lucky Punjab Sweets at your service.

46:34.791 --> 46:35.625
Okay great, thanks.

46:35.708 --> 46:36.541
How much is it?

46:36.625 --> 46:38.208
Special. 55.

46:39.166 --> 46:40.291
Keep the change.

46:40.375 --> 46:41.250
Thanks.

46:41.333 --> 46:44.166
Oh and on the bottom is the ginger beef.

46:44.250 --> 46:45.166
What ginger beef?

46:45.250 --> 46:46.625
That's for me.

46:46.708 --> 46:47.625
Thank you.

46:47.708 --> 46:48.583
[in Punjabi] God protect you.

46:48.666 --> 46:49.750
[Parm] Rup?

46:51.458 --> 46:52.291
Rup?

46:53.083 --> 46:53.916
Rup!

46:54.000 --> 46:55.125
[indistinct chanting]

46:55.208 --> 46:56.333
What, what, what?

46:57.500 --> 47:00.041
What are you doing? They're doing a <i>paath</i>.
You can't eat that here.

47:00.125 --> 47:03.083
Well, I gotta eat, man, you know?

47:03.166 --> 47:04.125
Take it outside. Okay?

47:04.208 --> 47:05.250
Just get it out of here.

47:05.333 --> 47:06.333
It's freezing outside.

47:06.416 --> 47:07.583
Are you serious?

47:07.666 --> 47:08.916
I am serious.

47:11.375 --> 47:12.375
Can I get a fork?

47:12.458 --> 47:13.791
Is that allowed?

47:14.833 --> 47:15.833
[silverware clanks]

47:20.833 --> 47:22.458
[indistinct chanting]

47:22.541 --> 47:26.208
[in Punjabi] Auntie, I’ll do that.

47:28.708 --> 47:30.916
[Auntie crying]

47:31.000 --> 47:32.166
[Parm] Puaji.

47:32.250 --> 47:35.916
[in Punjabi] I used to always
take care of your father.

47:37.083 --> 47:41.250
[in Punjabi] He used to remind me
of a little doll.

47:41.333 --> 47:45.208
[in Punjabi] You remind me so much of him.

47:45.291 --> 47:48.958
[in Punjabi] You’re such a good boy.

48:08.125 --> 48:08.958
Wow.

48:10.041 --> 48:11.791
Impressive set up.

48:11.875 --> 48:13.791
Parm made some calls.

48:14.708 --> 48:17.208
Thanks for agreeing to this.

48:20.500 --> 48:22.083
He looks better.

48:22.166 --> 48:25.708
He's hydrated and nourished,
but he's certainly not better.

48:25.791 --> 48:26.791
Lily.

48:26.875 --> 48:28.333
I'll be helping care for
your father until other

48:28.416 --> 48:30.250
arrangements are made.

48:31.541 --> 48:32.666
Thanks, but we're good.

48:32.750 --> 48:34.416
We got this.

48:34.500 --> 48:36.083
Oh, Mona, we're not good.

48:36.166 --> 48:38.000
If you're insisting on
keeping Dad here instead

48:38.083 --> 48:41.000
of a hospital, we need Lily's help.

48:42.583 --> 48:43.750
I can take care of him, Sandy.

48:43.833 --> 48:46.125
Caring for a cancer patient
and caring for a coma patient

48:46.208 --> 48:49.791
in his condition are
very different things.

48:54.541 --> 48:57.041
Holler if you need anything.

49:03.833 --> 49:05.416
He hates the radio.

49:10.208 --> 49:12.583
[soft music plays]

49:21.125 --> 49:23.250
[indistinct chattering]

49:23.333 --> 49:27.000
[in Punjabi] Girl, get married, why are
you determined to kill your father?

49:34.958 --> 49:37.458
We just ran out of coffee.

49:37.541 --> 49:38.375
Sip?

49:39.916 --> 49:41.750
No. It's okay.

49:41.833 --> 49:42.666
Um…

49:48.166 --> 49:50.916
I'll just have some generic cola.

49:51.875 --> 49:53.083
Hm.

49:53.166 --> 49:54.541
Good choice.

49:54.625 --> 49:57.875
Um, can we talk to you for a second?

49:57.958 --> 49:58.916
[Mona] Okay?

49:59.000 --> 50:00.333
Good. Come, follow me.

50:10.166 --> 50:11.500
What did I do now?

50:11.583 --> 50:12.916
[All] Nothing.

50:16.000 --> 50:17.708
So, good news.

50:17.791 --> 50:18.958
Remember Woody?

50:19.041 --> 50:19.916
Like Woody woody.

50:20.000 --> 50:21.250
[Rup] Like Woody-Woody.

50:21.333 --> 50:22.916
Yeah, okay. [laughs]

50:23.000 --> 50:24.541
[Rup] He's a developer in Regina, okay?

50:24.625 --> 50:26.791
Now, he says the market
is kinda slow these days,

50:26.875 --> 50:29.208
but an area like this
one's always gonna do well

50:29.291 --> 50:33.375
in the long-term and, for the right price,

50:33.458 --> 50:37.500
he'd be interested in buying this place.

50:37.583 --> 50:39.791
And do what with it?

50:39.875 --> 50:41.333
Tear it down.

50:41.416 --> 50:43.041
Build condos?

50:43.125 --> 50:44.291
What about Dad?

50:44.375 --> 50:46.333
We need to be realistic, Mona.

50:46.416 --> 50:48.500
Parm spoke to the doctors this morning and

50:48.583 --> 50:50.916
he wasn't optimistic.

50:51.000 --> 50:52.625
Well, why don't we
see how he does before

50:52.708 --> 50:53.541
we plan his funeral?

50:53.625 --> 50:55.166
[Sandy] That's not what we're doing.

50:55.250 --> 50:56.125
You're kicking him out of the house,

50:56.208 --> 50:57.833
because you think he's gonna die.

50:57.916 --> 50:59.000
-He is gonna die.
-No.

50:59.083 --> 51:00.666
No, hold up hold up.
Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

51:00.750 --> 51:02.541
Let's get back to the topic. Listen.

51:02.625 --> 51:04.291
Mona, the house is falling apart.

51:04.375 --> 51:05.958
Okay? It's falling apart.

51:06.083 --> 51:07.750
Dad can't live here.

51:10.500 --> 51:14.583
[clears throat] What about me?

51:15.958 --> 51:20.500
[Rup] We split the profits,
you buy yourself a nice place.

51:20.583 --> 51:23.666
We also feel you should think about

51:25.708 --> 51:26.958
getting a job.

51:27.041 --> 51:27.875
Sandy.

51:27.958 --> 51:30.500
You've been out of the
job market for seven years.

51:30.583 --> 51:32.416
Or, go back to school.

51:33.708 --> 51:34.708
I'm a writer.

51:34.791 --> 51:37.125
You need a job that pays.

51:37.208 --> 51:38.166
I'm a writer.

51:38.250 --> 51:40.833
Okay.
Can we think about selling this house?

51:40.916 --> 51:43.916
Deals like this don't come often.
Let's just sell.

51:44.000 --> 51:46.291
A woman your age should
not be living at home

51:46.375 --> 51:49.208
with her father with no
job and no prospects.

51:49.291 --> 51:52.125
We're not judging you, okay?
We're not judging you.

51:52.208 --> 51:54.833
I'm sorry that I didn't
have time to go on a date

51:54.916 --> 51:57.916
because I was too busy
keeping our father alive.

51:58.000 --> 51:59.583
And taking him to chemo.

51:59.666 --> 52:02.958
And making sure he didn't
choke on his own vomit.

52:03.041 --> 52:05.708
Where the hell were you
guys the last seven years?

52:05.791 --> 52:08.375
-We flew in all the time.
-[Mona] Yeah, but you weren't here.

52:08.458 --> 52:10.625
We checked in every day.

52:11.583 --> 52:14.125
You barely called us back
unless you needed money.

52:14.208 --> 52:16.625
Yeah, but you weren't here.

52:16.708 --> 52:18.041
[Parm] Mona, we never
asked you to be the one

52:18.125 --> 52:19.291
to take care of him.

52:19.375 --> 52:22.791
[Sandy] You need to face reality, Mona.

52:26.625 --> 52:27.958
You're a cunt.

52:31.250 --> 52:33.541
[Rup] Wait! Mona!
Mona, what about the house?

52:36.625 --> 52:37.791
What was that?

52:39.541 --> 52:41.208
What was that?

52:41.291 --> 52:42.583
Where were you guys?

52:42.666 --> 52:44.125
You didn't have my back.

52:44.208 --> 52:45.875
You just left me to hang out there and dry

52:45.958 --> 52:47.083
and make me look like the bad guy.

52:47.166 --> 52:48.416
-Sandy, Sandy.
-As you always, you always.

52:48.500 --> 52:50.208
You're going in on her about
employment and job prospects.

52:50.291 --> 52:51.750
You always put it on me.

52:51.833 --> 52:53.583
You always make me say the hard shit.

52:53.666 --> 52:55.250
Sandy! Listen to me.

52:55.333 --> 52:56.875
The conversation was about the house!
Selling the house!

52:56.958 --> 52:58.125
-It was about the house…
-That's it, that's it, Sandy.

52:58.208 --> 52:59.250
…and then it became about
something else,

52:59.333 --> 53:01.125
and you never have my back!

53:01.208 --> 53:03.125
You took it that way!
Am I going crazy here?

53:03.208 --> 53:04.791
Parm, wait! Parm!

53:04.875 --> 53:06.875
Sandy, you can't just
attack somebody like that!

53:06.958 --> 53:08.916
[Sandy] Somebody
needs to tell her the truth.

53:12.083 --> 53:13.875
[knock thudding]

53:13.958 --> 53:15.625
-Mr. Rop.
-It's Rup.

53:15.708 --> 53:17.291
-Hey.
-Good news.

53:17.375 --> 53:18.833
I've seen this problem before.

53:18.916 --> 53:23.416
Bad news, you'll have to redo the pipes
out to mid-street level.

53:23.500 --> 53:24.416
Probably.

53:24.500 --> 53:25.833
It's not a small job.

53:25.916 --> 53:27.916
Okay. Well, how much does it cost?

53:28.000 --> 53:30.375
Just ballpark it for me, Patrick, please.

53:30.458 --> 53:32.208
[Patrick] About 25.

